HEADWORD: Carney
<hw>Car"ney</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>carneus</ets> flesh.]</ety> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A disease of
horses, in which the mouth is so furred that the afflicted animal can
not eat.</def>⟦br⟧
